After running Docker image,we have to go inside Dockernodejs folder

and run these command step by step

```
npm install -g bower  

npm install   

bower install --allow-root

service postgresql start

sudo -u postgres psql

ALTER USER postgres PASSWORD 'root';

CREATE TABLE scl_user(user_id serial PRIMARY KEY,username VARCHAR (50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,password VARCHAR (50) NOT NULL,email VARCHAR (355) UNIQUE NOT NULL,mobile_no VARCHAR (15) NOT NULL,created_on TIMESTAMP,updated_by TIMESTAMP,last_login TIMESTAMP);

```
and after these command ,the final command 

```

node server.js

```

After this you have to go browser and see your application is running with command

127.0.0.1:8080

